Household properties worth millions of naira were in the wee hours of Sunday engulfed as a residential building was razed along Atufe Road by Major Bowen Junction, Sapele, headquarters of Sapele Local Government Area of Delta State. PUNCH Metro, however, gathered that the cause of the inferno was yet to be ascertained as of the time of filing this report. Witnesses said that the building was 80 percent destroyed before fire fighters from Delta State Fire Service arrived at the scene to curtail the inferno. It was gathered that the troubled residents could not reach officials of the State Fire Service till after much havoc had been done. However, operatives of Seplat Fire Service, an oil firm in Sapele, were said to have later responded to distress calls from well-meaning people in the community. It was gathered that the Seplat Fire Service officials eventually succeeded in putting out the raging fire. The Police Public Relations Officer from Delta State Command, Bright Edafe, could not be reached for comments on the incident, as of the time of filing this report Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com